				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Does health insurance cover plastic surgery?</h3>
					<p>Insurance may cover plastic surgery when it is medically necessary, such as breast reconstruction after mastectomy, functional rhinoplasty, or repair of congenital deformities. Purely cosmetic procedures are generally not covered. We can help you determine if your procedure may qualify for insurance coverage.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>Why is plastic surgery cheaper in India than in other countries?</h3>
					<p>India offers significantly lower costs due to lower overhead expenses, reduced facility costs, and a competitive market. Despite the lower prices, Indian plastic surgeons like Dr. Johar are highly trained and experienced, offering world-class care at a fraction of international prices.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="faq-item">
					<h3>How do I choose a surgeon based on cost?</h3>
